# Will You Be My Valentine, Marji? ğŸ’•

A cute and interactive Valentine's Day website to ask your special someone to be your Valentine with a playful twist!

![Valentine's Day Website](https://img.shields.io/badge/Valentine's-Day-Love-red) 
![Status](https://img.shields.io/badge/status-active-success) 
![License](https://img.shields.io/badge/license-MIT-blue)

## Features âœ¨

- **Beautiful Design**: Romantic pink and red color scheme with floating hearts animation
- **Interactive "No" Button**: Playfully runs away from the cursor, making it impossible to click!
- **Celebration Mode**: When "Yes" is clicked, a celebration screen appears with confetti and animated hearts
- **Responsive**: Works on both desktop and mobile devices
- **Personalized**: Easily customizable with your loved one's name

## How to Use ğŸš€

1. Clone this repository:
   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/yourusername/valentine-proposal-marji.git
   ```

2. Open `index.html` in your web browser to view the website

3. To customize with a different name:
   - Open `index.html` in a text editor
   - Find the line with "Marji" and replace it with your Valentine's name

## Screenshots ğŸ“¸

The website features:
- A romantic background with floating hearts
- A central card with the question "Will you be my Valentine?"
- Two buttons: "Yes" and "No"
- The "No" button playfully avoids the cursor
- A celebration screen when "Yes" is clicked

## Customization ğŸ¨

You can easily customize this project by:
- Changing the background image in the CSS
- Modifying the colors in the CSS variables
- Adding your own message when "Yes" is clicked
- Changing the celebration animation

